00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,100
You mean, antidepressants.

651
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:56,800
Yes. They were in his apartment,

652
00:29:56,900 --> 00:29:58,300
But he also had a prescription

653
00:29:58,300 --> 00:30:01,260
For some pretty hardy tranquilizers.

654
00:30:01,300 --> 00:30:03,600
Now there's contraindications,

655
00:30:03,700 --> 00:30:06,500
Meaning that's a very bad combo.

656
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:08,600
He had to go to two pharmacies and two doctors

657
00:30:08,700 --> 00:30:10,200
To get them filled.

658
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:11,200
How do you know that?

659
00:30:11,300 --> 00:30:12,500
I'm a doctor.

660
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:13,900
I called a few drug stores in hamilton.

661
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,900
You're a ph. D., not an m.D.

662
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,800
I'm not named dr. Hellar either,

663
00:30:17,900 --> 00:30:19,200
But they didn't need to know that.

664
00:30:19,300 --> 00:30:22,500
Ok. So we know that he gave his best friend drugs.

665
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:25,900
Did he have any idea that the combination would kill him?

666
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:28,500
I should have changed.

667
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:30,000
It is this guy's memorial.

668
00:30:30,100 --> 00:30:31,400
It's just a get-Together with old friends.

669
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:34,100
Besides,i don't think we'll be staying long.

