00:38:12,100 --> 00:38:14,700
Maybe that will help.

824
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:17,100
I don't think she wants revenge.

825
00:38:17,200 --> 00:38:19,800
I think she wants to know what it was like

826
00:38:19,900 --> 00:38:22,400
For her husband

827
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:24,100
In those final moments.

828
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:33,500
Maybe she'll take comfort in knowing he wasn't alone.

829
00:38:54,300 --> 00:38:57,500
All those years, you held it in

830
00:38:57,600 --> 00:38:59,900
For grace, for both of them.

831
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:05,500
It's all i could think about

832
00:39:05,500 --> 00:39:06,800
My whole adult life.

833
00:39:06,900 --> 00:39:10,800
Well,now you can just let go.

834
00:39:10,900 --> 00:39:13,500
But what comes next?

835
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:15,800
The light.

836
00:39:15,900 --> 00:39:17,600
What's that like?

837
00:39:17,700 --> 00:39:19,900
I don't know.

838
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:23,900
D- Doesn't that s- Scare you?

839
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,700
The light doesn't scare me.

840
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:28,300
No,no,no.

841
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:30,300
I'm talking about the unknown.

842
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:31,800
I'm just like anyone else.

843
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:34,200
Of course it scares me.

844
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:35,200
Yeah.

845
00:39:35,300 --> 00:39:38,100
But it's ok to be scared.

846
00:39:45,600 --> 00:39:47,200
Wow!

847
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:59,400
Take care of them, will you,all of them?

848
00:39:59,500 --> 00:40:02,000
I will.

849
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:05,500
You're all right, meloony gordon.

850
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,700
Don't let anyone tell you otherwise.

851
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:40,900
Hey.

852
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:43,000
What are you doing?

853
00:40:43,100 --> 00:40:44,000
I lost your tear sheet,

854
00:40:44,100 --> 00:40:46,400
So i'm kind of winging it right now.

855
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:48,500
No. I mean,i thought we were gonna wait

856
00:40:48,600 --> 00:40:49,700
Until i got pregnant

857
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:52,400
Because then we would still have 9 months.

858
00:40:52,500 --> 00:40:54,100
Yeah. Yeah, that was my plan.

859
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:57,400
Very logical, but,uh,didn't seem to

860
00:40:57,400 --> 00:40:59,200
Make you very happy.

861
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:04,000
It's not you.

862
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:07,800
It's what i do.

863
00:41:07,800 --> 00:41:10,100
Silly fears and anxieties,

864
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:12,700
Stupid things that ghosts say.

865
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:14,100
Like what?

866
00:41:17,300 --> 00:41:18,500
What?

867
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:26,200
That there might be a price for me to pay

868
00:41:26,300 --> 00:41:30,500
For what i do, putting myself

869
00:41:30,600 --> 00:41:34,400
In places where i might not belong.

870
00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:35,700
What kind of places?

871
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:38,800
The unknown...

872
00:41:38,900 --> 00:41:40,400
Death.

873
00:41:42,300 --> 00:41:46,400
You know,that's exactly why we do this.

874
00:41:46,500 --> 00:41:48,400
Yeah. This project, all of it.

875
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:50,000
I was wrong, you were right.

876
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:51,000
Why?

877
00:41:51,100 --> 00:41:52,100
Because of what you do.

878
00:41:52,200 --> 00:41:54,500
Every day,you know, you believe.

879
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:55,700
We should believe that the right thing

880
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,100
Is gonna happen no matter what,

881
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:59,800
So we just keep pushing and pushing until it does.

882
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:02,900
What if it doesn't?

883
00:42:02,900 --> 00:42:04,600
Well,then we push some more.

884
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:09,400
Where did you learn to be so brave?

